OL,3,CGovernment to make #6bn welfare
OL,4,Csavings with benefits shake-up
OL,6,FLiz Kendall, the work and pensions
OL,7,Fsecretary, has argued that the welfare
OL,8,Fsystem is broken and it is critical to
OL,9,Fget more people into work. But the
OL,10,Fchanges are likely to be hugely
OL,11,Fcontroversial, including with Labour
OL,12,Fbackbenchers.
OL,14,FThe radical package of reforms will
OL,15,Fsee:
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
