OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F317A1741547777
OL,3,CGovernment to make #6bn welfare
OL,4,Csavings with benefits shake-up
OL,6,F"PIP exists because life costs more if
OL,7,Fyou are disabled. Those costs won't
OL,8,Fdisappear if the government squeezes
OL,9,Feligibility. Many disabled people use
OL,10,FPIP to get to and from work and to pay
OL,11,Ffor essential equipment like mobility
OL,12,Faids.
OL,14,F"Making it harder to get benefits will
OL,15,Fjust push even more disabled people
OL,16,Finto poverty, not into jobs.
OL,18,F"The Chancellor has a choice ` cut
OL,19,Fbenefits and increase poverty, or
OL,20,Finvest in an equal future for disabled
OL,21,Fpeople.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
